						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/University-of-Groningen-talent-grant-PhD-fellowship-programme" title="University of Groningen talent grant: PhD fellowship programme" alt="link">University of Groningen talent grant: PhD fellowship programme</a></h2>

	
					<p>This programme enables junior researchers to do part of their PhD research at the University of Groningen for periods of a maximum of six months each year within a four year period. During this period, the researcher remains in the employ of their home institution in the country of origin. Grants will cover expenses incurred in travelling to and from the Netherlands (max. of four times) and the living costs during the stay. A moderate research budget can be granted, if judged necessary by the academic supervisor. PhD candidates from a university that has signed a co-operation agreement will be given preferential treatment. There are also grants available for a brief stay in Groningen (max. three months). These are intended for junior researchers who wish to formulate a research proposal or academic staff who want to spend a sabbatical leave at the University of Groningen. <b>Applications are accepted throughout the year.</b></p>
							<p><span class="date">4/11/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/University-of-Groningen-talent-grant-PhD-fellowship-programme">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/Call-for-research-proposals-Radio-convergence-and-development-research-project" title="Call for research proposals: Radio, convergence and development research project" alt="link">Call for research proposals: Radio, convergence and development research project</a></h2>

	
					<p>A new three-year research programme funded by DFID, and <a href="http://www.idrc.ca/acacia/ev-139447-201-1-DO_TOPIC.html" target="_blank">IDRC</a> will support research on how the purposes and functions of traditional radio in Africa are influenced by new information and communication technologies (ICTs), notably mobile phones and the internet. While other ICTs continue to expand their reach, it is clear that radio remains the dominant mass-medium in Africa. However, the dramatic increase in mobile phone penetration and interactive exchange of content across Africa is ushering in a significant change in communications and a range of positive and negative development outcomes. Research is needed to establish baseline data, to collect impact evidence, and forecast future trends. <b>The deadline for application is January 8th, 2010. </b>Research grants will be awarded in early 2010. This is an initiative through the IDRC/DFID ICT4D programme, administered by the Centre for Media and Transitional Societies, Carleton University, Canada.</p>
							<p><span class="date">4/11/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/Call-for-research-proposals-Radio-convergence-and-development-research-project">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/Call-for-applications-20-PhD-scholarhips-at-the-International-Center-for-Development-and-Decent-Work-ICDD" title="Call for applications: 20 PhD scholarhips at the International Center for Development and Decent Work (ICDD)" alt="link">Call for applications: 20 PhD scholarhips at the International Center for Development and Decent Work (ICDD)</a></h2>

	
					<p><i>Graduate School of Socio-Ecological Research for Development</i>&nbsp;ICDD is an interdisciplinary and international scientific network of excellence with the head office located at the University of Kassel, Germany and has partner universities in Latin America, Africa and Asia. ICDD is funded under the programme Higher Education Excellence in Development Co-operation, launched by the German Federal Ministry for Economic Cooperation and Development through the German Academic Exchange Service. Under its Graduate School of Socio-Ecological Research for Development, ICDD invites applications for 20 PhD scholarship positions for students from <a href="http://cms.uni-kassel.de/unicms/fileadmin/groups/w_460500/dateien/DAC_Countries.pdf" target="_blank">various countries</a>. <b>Deadline for application is 15 November 2009.</b></p>
							<p><span class="date">4/11/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/Call-for-applications-20-PhD-scholarhips-at-the-International-Center-for-Development-and-Decent-Work-ICDD">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
